COMPONENT NAME: LKM Attunity to SQL COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: 10.1.3.5.0 and above
DESCRIPTION - This module reads selected data from the Attunity Stream staging area of Attunity Streams and writes the result into the target temporary table, which is created dynamically. - Loads data to any ISO-92 compliant target database.
REQUIREMENTS - PK_LIST is a mandatory option and must contains at list one column name.
OPTIONS (Refer to the Option descriptions for more information on each option) - PK_LIST (*): contains the list of columns to use as the Primary Key - DELETE_TEMPORARY_OBJECTS: delete or not the temporary objects after processing.
LIMITATIONS - This Knowledge Module is NOT RECOMMENDED when using LARGE VOLUMES. Other specific modules using Bulk utilities (SQL*LOADER, BULK INSERT...) or direct links (DBLINKS, Linked Servers...) are usually more efficient.

Set this option to NO, if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration.
Useful for debugging.

Source columns list that holds the primary key of the journalized table.
Use SQL syntax and separate with a comma (',') each column.

import java.sql as sql import java.lang as lang import time
srcCx = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("SRC")
selMaxContext = '''select max(context) CONTEXT from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%> '''.replace('\\','') stmtSelMaxContext = srcCx.createStatement() rsSelMaxContext = stmtSelMaxContext.executeQuery(selMaxContext) if rsSelMaxContext.next(): maxCtx = rsSelMaxContext.getString('CONTEXT') rsSelMaxContext.close() if maxCtx <> 'None': insMaxContext = '''insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%> values ('%s')'''.replace('\\','') % maxCtx psMaxContext = srcCx.prepareStatement(insMaxContext) psMaxContext.executeUpdate() psMaxContext.close()

select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]\t[ALIAS_SEP] [CX_COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "")%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%>, (select <%=odiRef.getOption("PK_LIST")%>, max(context) CTX from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%>,<%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%> where context <= ctx group by <%=odiRef.getOption("PK_LIST")%>) T
where (T.ctx = context) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getJoin()%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=odiRef.getHaving()%>
delete from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%> where context <= (select ctx from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%>)
